review:
Quite a unique mix of tower defense and isometric action RPG in The Incredible Adventures of Van Helsing universe. Gameplay wise two different genres surprisingly seamlessly complement each other and create unusual synergy between your character build and towers selection. Can easily recommend for any action RPG or tower defense fan.

Pros:
- Three unique classes;
- Steam Workshop support;
- Good soundtrack;
- Decent visuals;
- A lot of skills and tower types;
- Co-op;

Cons:
- Bad optimisation;
- Only 13 maps (but each map have multiple difficulty modes);
- Difficulty spikes;
